THE former President Jakaya Kikwete is expected to grace the ‘Brazuka Charity Marathon’ ahead of its flag off on September 15th in Dar es Salaam. It is a charity marathon as that aims to raise funds to support medical treatments to under five years old children with cardiac problems. The Coordinator for the event, Nasikiwa Berya said in Dar es Salaam yesterday, the goal for the Marathon is to collect over 100m/-which is needed to support medical treatment to 512 children with cardiac complications at the Jakaya Kikwete Cardiac Institute (JKCI), at the Muhimbili National Hospital (MNH). The Local Hip Hop musician, Hamis Mwinjuma popularly known as ‘Mwana FA’ has confirmed to be the Ambassador of the charity marathon and he will participate and perform during the event. “The cost of medical treatment to a child with cardiac complications is not less than 3m/-, there are many parents who can’t afford the costs, may I ask the community to volunteer and help them by contributing as much money as we can,” she said. She said there will be three types of races, the first being the 5km fun run, while the second will be the 10km race while the main event will cover 15kilometres. The registration fee is 5,000/-for 5km, 10,000/-for 10km and 15,000/-for 15km marathoners. Registration will be for four days at Mlimani City Mall or through the website www.brazukabenki. com. Speaking on the same occasion the event’s Ambassador, Mwana FA has invited the members of community to come out to participate in the event and donate the money to enable children with cardiac problem get treatment. The sponsors for the Brazuka Charity Marathon 2019 are E Fm Media, MzukaBet, T-Pesa, Coca cola and AfriDecor. The marathon expecting to start at 5:00 am at the Jakaya Mrisho Kikwete Youth Park.